Hello! I'm Nala, your health and wellness coach. I'm so glad you're here and ready to start this journey with me. What's your name?
jade

Hi Jade! It's wonderful to meet you. Let me tell you a bit about what we'll be doing together.

This is a 4-week program where we'll meet once a week for coaching sessions, just like this one. We'll work together to set personalized health goals that matter to you, and I'll help you develop strategies to achieve them. Each week when we meet, we'll check in on your progress, adjust as needed, and keep you moving forward. Between our weekly sessions, you'll be working on your goals independently, and we'll discuss how things went when we meet again.

Does that sound good? Do you have any questions about how the program works before we dive in?
no
Great! Before we dive into goal setting, I'd love to get to know you better. Tell me a bit about yourself?
Im a college student and i work so im incredibly busy

I can imagine how demanding that must be, juggling both college and work. That's a lot on your plate. 

What does your current exercise routine look like, if you have one?
i walk 3 times a week
That's great that you're getting out for walks three times a week, especially with such a busy schedule. How long are those walks typically?
30 min

That's a solid routine, Jade. Getting 30 minutes of walking three times a week is definitely beneficial, especially when you're balancing college and work.

How are your sleep habits? How many hours are you typically getting per night, and how would you describe the quality?
i get 8 hours of sleep and its pretty good

That's really good to hear that you're prioritizing sleep and getting a solid 8 hours with good quality. Sleep is so important, especially with your busy schedule.

What are your current eating habits like? For example, how many meals do you typically eat in a day, and what does that usually look like for you?
i eat 3 meals a day with whatever is kinda there

I appreciate you sharing that. When you say "whatever is kinda there," it sounds like your meals might be pretty spontaneous. Can you walk me through what you ate yesterday or today, just to give me a better sense of what a typical day looks like for you?
yesterday morning i had some pastries, lunch i had a subway sandwich, and dinner i had chicken with pasta

Thanks for sharing that, Jade. It sounds like you're getting three meals in, which is great. I can see there's some variety there with the sandwich, chicken, and pasta.

What do you like to do in your free time when you're not busy with college or work?
i like to crochet

That's wonderful, Jade. Crocheting is such a calming and creative activity. It's great that you have something you enjoy that helps you unwind.

Now that I have a better sense of your daily routine, what specific health or wellness goal would you like to focus on during our time together?
i want to work on my exercise

I love that you want to focus on exercise, Jade. That's a great area to work on. Right now, your goal is pretty general, so let's make it more specific and actionable so you have a clear path forward.

What kind of exercise are you thinking about, and how often would you like to do it?
i want to start jogging and maybe 3x a week

That's a great start, Jade! Jogging three times a week is a solid foundation. Now let's get even more specific so you know exactly what success looks like.

How long do you want to jog each time, and over what timeframe do you want to commit to this - like for the next two weeks, or the next month?
20 min for the next week
Perfect, Jade! So let me make sure I've got this right: you want to jog for 20 minutes, three times over the next week. Is that correct?
yes

That's a clear and achievable goal, Jade! Jogging for 20 minutes three times this week is specific, measurable, and has a clear timeframe. Now let's think about making it stick.

What days this week do you think would work best for your jogging sessions, and what might get in the way of completing them?
MWF

Monday, Wednesday, and Friday - that's a great schedule with rest days built in! Now, thinking about those specific days, what obstacles or challenges might come up that could make it harder to get your jogs in?
I think just how busy I am might be something i need to think about
That's a really important thing to consider. Can you tell me more about what makes those days busy - is it work, family commitments, or something else that tends to fill up your time?
i just have finals week coming up

Finals week is definitely a big time crunch. Given that stress and time pressure, do you think jogging three times this week is realistic, or would it be better to adjust your goal to something more manageable during finals?
i want to try the 3 days and see how it goes

I really appreciate your determination to try for those three days even during finals week. So just to make sure I have this right, your goal is to jog for 20 minutes on Monday, Wednesday, and Friday this coming week, is that correct?
yes
Great, thank you for confirming. Now, on a scale of 1 to 10, how confident do you feel about achieving this goal of jogging 20 minutes on those three days this week?
A 7 is a solid level of confidence, and it shows you're being realistic about the challenge of finals week. What would need to happen to bump that confidence up to an 8 or 9?
i think i just need to try that

That makes total sense, sometimes you just need to get out there and do it to build that confidence. Would you like to set another goal to work on this week, or would you prefer to focus just on getting those three jogs in during finals?
no

Perfect, focusing on one goal during finals week is a smart choice. Now let's talk about how you'll remember to work on your jogging goal this week. How will you keep track of it or remind yourself to do it?
i will set reminders on my phone
Phone reminders are a great tool, especially during a busy week. What days and times are you thinking of setting those reminders for your three jogs?
The mornings of my jogs for 9 am
Perfect, so you'll have reminders set for 9 am on the mornings you plan to jog. Is there anything else you'd like to talk about before we wrap up today?
no

Great work today, Jade. Just to recap, your goal is to jog for 20 minutes three days this week, and you'll use phone reminders at 9 am on those mornings to help you stay on track. I know finals week is busy, but you rated your confidence at 7 out of 10, which shows you believe you can make this happen.
